<title>USA: CSCE decreases margins on all cocoa futures.</title>
<headline>CSCE decreases margins on all cocoa futures.</headline>
<dateline>NEW YORK 1997-05-06</dateline>
<text>
<p>The Coffee, Sugar and Cocoa Exchange said it decreased the margins on all cocoa contracts by $200, to $600.</p>
<p>The May and July 1997 contracts include no spot charges.</p>
<p>The change is effective May 6.</p>
<p>For customers who are not exchange members or a member of the trade, margins will be 140 percent above trade rates, the CSCE said.</p>
<p>((--Patricia Avidan, New York Commodity Desk 212 859-1640))</p>
